    <section id="caesar">
        <h2>Caesar Cipher</h2>
        <img src="images/Caesar_wheel.png" alt="Image of Caesar wheel" width="350" height="350">
        <article>
            The Caesar Cipher or Shift Cipher is one of the oldest and 
            and simplest ciphers.  It is a substitution cipher that will take
            each letter of the Plaintext and "shift" along the alphabet
            a pre-determined number of spaces and selects that character 
            as the Ciphertext.
        </article>
       
