    <section id="viginere">
        <h2>Viginere Cipher</h2>
        <img src="images/vig_table.jpg" alt="Image of Vigenere table" width="320" height="320">
            <article>
                The Viginere Cipher is a more complicated form of Caesar Cipher.  
                It encrypts the Plaintext by using a series of interwoven Caesar ciphers based 
                upon each character of the key word to produce the end Ciphertext.  This
                cipher was first postulated by Giovan Battista Ballaso but was misattributeted
                to Blaise de Vigenere, hence the name.
            </article>
    
            <div id="plaintext_input">
                <p>Please enter the text to be encrypted or decrypted.<br><input rows="1" cols="100" autofocus id="viginere_plain_text"></input></p>
