        <img src="images/adfgvx_table.jpg" alt="Image of A D F G V X table" width="350" height="350">
            <article>
                The ADFGVX Cipher was used by the German Army during World War 1.
                It is a modified version of the Polybius Cipher which used the characters
                A D F G V and X.  The reason these letters were chosen is because they
                are very different from one another in Morse Code.  It was invented by
                Fritz Nebel and brought into service in 1918.
            </article>
    
