        <img src="images/polybuis_table.jpg" alt="Image of Polybius table" width="350" height="350">
            <article>
                The Polybius square is an ancient method for fractionating plaintext so that
                characters can be represented by a smaller set of symbols.  It was created by
                Ancient Greeks Cleoxenus and Democleitus and later perfected by the greek
                historian Polybius.  The most recent use of this method of communication was
                a modified version called the "Knock Code" by USA POW's in the Vietnam War.
            </article>
    
            <div id="plaintext_input">
