            <article>
                Base64 Encoding is a form of binary conversion.  It uses the ASCII format
                to represent the binary data in a-z, A-Z, 0-9 and the special characters + /, 
                64 characters in total.  This is not cipher but a way to encode data, it
                can however be further encrypted using a varity of hashing functions.
            </article>
    
