        <img src="images/morse_table.jpg" alt="Image of Morse Code table" width="300" height="250">
            <article>
                Morse Code is a method of character encoding using two different signals, a dot
                and a dash.  By combining these dots and dashes into various patterns it
                can encode latin alphabet characters and arabic numerals.  It is named after
                the inventor of Electronic Telegraph, Samuel Morse.  One of the well known
                message sent by Morse is ... --- ... S.O.S (Save Our Souls).
            </article>
    
